{
  "title": "Social differentials in speed-premium effects in childbearing in Sweden",
  "abstract": "In Sweden, parents receive a parental-leave allowance of a high percentage (currently 80%) of their pre-birth salary for about a year in connection with any birth. If they space their births sufficiently closely, they avoid a reduction in the allowance",
